## 2. The sharing model (the core idea)

Three tiers. One policy: **who goes first, who shares the rest, who's just
visiting.**

1. **KPFK — priority.** Right of way: first whenever it has work. Unmetered.
   Priority is **work-conserving** — KPFK is idle most of the quarter, and when it
   is, the lower tiers get the whole pipe. No slot is reserved/wasted for a
   usually-quiet station.
2. **Paying peers — fair share.** Converted stations are unmetered and split
   whatever KPFK isn't using, **evenly**. Fairness is correct *here* (it was wrong
   as a top-level goal) precisely because these stations are equals — all paying.
3. **Demo stations — capped.** A prospect on trial runs under an adjustable daily
   allowance, time-boxed (~30 days default), and cannot crowd the tiers above.

**Demo and full are the same dial.** There is one per-station processing
allowance: throttled = demo, unlimited = full. "Graduating" is turning the dial
up — not flipping a mode. The dial is adjustable per station, with a sane default
and a duration (extend / end early / convert). Keep it to *one allowance + a
duration per station* — do **not** rebuild a per-stage tiered metering panel.

**Default demo heuristic:** enough to process a prospect's *recent* programming
and feel the value within the month — not enough to churn their whole back-catalog
into the shared pipe (the onboarding surge is the real contention event).

---

## 3. Locked decisions

| Decision | Choice |
|---|---|
| Sharing policy | KPFK priority (work-conserving) → paying peers fair-share → demos capped |
| Demo vs full | One adjustable per-station allowance dial + duration; demo = throttled, full = unlimited |
| Daily window | Calendar day, **midnight `America/Los_Angeles`** (DST-correct, never fixed −8) |
| Pause behavior | **Graceful** — finish running job, start nothing new; ingest keeps running |
| Hard stop | Kills everything incl. ingest; **aborts in-flight with clean revert**; reversible; confirm-gated |
| Concurrency | Drop steady/catch-up toggle; fixed floor **≥ 2** for isolation; **KPFK job priority** for production-first |
| Confirmation | Display and enforcement read the **same counter** |
| Billing model | Flat monthly per station + unmetered; no usage meter for billing |

